<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-07-26T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-07-26T14:00:00-05:00" n="778" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d778">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">825.00 Revolutions/7: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-07-26T14:00:00-05:00">July 26, 1931—2
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 4:09 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>79. President resigned and is still in Moneda. Already he has requested
                            asylum for his son-in-law and family and I have replied that I cannot
                            admit them to the Embassy unless they are threatened with physical
                            violence and then only temporarily. Civilian junta is forming. Tension
                            has been removed and there is public rejoicing throughout the city.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>